what's the origin of coke a cola dang liselle crack coca cola is a cola a type of carbonated soft drink sold in stores restaurants and vending machines in more than countries it is produced by the coca cola company nyse ko which is often referred to as simply coca cola or coke coke is the world's most recognizable brand according to businessweek originally intended as a patent medicine when it was invented in the late th century by john pemberton coca cola was bought out by businessman asa griggs candler whose marketing tactics led coke to its dominance of the world soft drink market throughout the th century although faced with criticisms of its health effects and various allegations of wrongdoing by the company coca cola has remained a popular soft drink to the present day the first coca cola recipe was invented in covington georgia by john stith pemberton originally as a cocawine called pemberton's french wine coca in he may have been inspired by the formidable success of european angelo mariani's cocawine vin mariani in when atlanta and fulton county passed prohibition legislation pemberton responded by developing coca cola essentially a carbonated non alcoholic version of french wine cola the beverage was named coca cola because originally the stimulant mixed in the beverage was coca leaves from south america in addition the drink was flavored using kola nuts also acting as the beverage's source of caffeine the first serving in cost us pemberton called for five ounces of coca leaf per gallon of syrup a significant dose whereas in candler claimed his formula altered extensively from pemberton's original contained only a tenth of this amount coca cola did once contain an estimated nine milligrams of cocaine per glass but in it was removed after coca cola started using instead of fresh leaves spent leaves the leftovers of the cocaine extraction process with cocaine trace levels left over at a molecular level to this day coca cola uses as an ingredient a non narcotic coca leaf extract prepared at a stepan company plant in maywood new jersey in the united states stepan company is the only manufacturing plant authorized by the federal government to import and process the coca plant Illegal drug trade The Coca-Cola Company Coffee New Coke Caffeine Beer Coca Tea Diet Coke Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs Wine Chocolate Rum Prohibition (drugs) Inca Kola Cola Irn-Bru Diet soda Moonshine Champagne (beverage) Convention on Psychotropic Substances Drink Arguments for and against drug prohibition Sugar Dr Pepper Carbon dioxide Red Bull Cannabis rescheduling in the United States Ice cream Ramen Tobacco smoking Cider Alcohol fuel Coca eradication McDonald's Moxie Breastfeeding Vitasoy Cannabis (drug) Patent medicine Milk Pisco French cuisine Recreational drug use Energy drink Peruvian cuisine Monsanto Food OK Soda Word of Wisdom Watermelon Hypoglycemia Milkshake Sake Sucralose Alcohol Hydrochloric acid Cigarette Clandestine chemistry Tobacco Hangover Controlled Substances Act Methamphetamine Nutmeg In-N-Out Burger Genericized trademark Martini cocktail Georgia (U.S. state) Plastic Bread Honey Peanut Iron Trademark Veganism Biodiesel Lithium salt Hydrogen economy Rooibos Nuclear power Atkins Nutritional Approach Aspartame Brewery Essential oil 